                <head>95. Editorial Note</head>
                <p>In two letters to Ambassador <persName corresp="#p_DE1">Durbrow</persName>,
                        <persName corresp="#p_ADV1">Daniel Anderson</persName>, Director of the
                    Office of Southeast Asian Affairs, informed the Ambassador that both the
                    Departments of Defense and State had approved as part of the fiscal year 1960
                    Military Assistance Program the allocation of 25 Navy AD–4 aircraft (one
                    squadron) to the Vietnamese Air Force. The Department of Defense, according to
                        <persName>Anderson</persName>, estimated that the first aircraft would be
                    delivered to Vietnam within 11 months and the last by 15 months. (Letters from
                        <persName>Anderson</persName> to <persName corresp="#p_DE1"
                        >Durbrow</persName>, November 20 and December 7; Department of State,
                    Vietnam Working Group Files: Lot 66 D 193, 109. <gloss target="#t_VN1"
                        >VN</gloss> 1960—Military Assistance)</p>
            </div>
